1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,280
I used only free AI for 30 days.

2
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:06,100
The honest breakdown nobody shows.

3
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:07,100
Hook.

4
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:09,300
0100-030.

5
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:13,880
For 30 days, I canceled every paid AI subscription.

6
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:16,359
No chat GPT+.

7
00:00:16,359 --> 00:00:17,859
No cloud pro.

8
00:00:17,859 --> 00:00:19,300
No mid-journey.

9
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:21,440
Not even a $5 tool.

10
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:27,800
I forced myself to build my entire workflow using only free local in cloud AI.

11
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,920
Some days I wanted to cry.

12
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:33,200
Other days I felt like I had hacked the matrix.

13
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:37,280
Here is the unfiltered truth about what actually works for free.

14
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:38,520
What fails?

15
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:42,240
And what nobody tells you about the hidden costs?

16
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,240
Content.

17
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,240
Section 1.

18
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:45,240
The rules I followed.

19
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:48,040
I set three simple rules.

20
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:49,240
Rule 1.

21
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:51,600
No paid AI services.

22
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,600
Rule 2.

23
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:55,880
No pirated accounts or shared logins.

24
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,079
Rule 3.

25
00:00:57,079 --> 00:01:00,640
If a free tool required a credit card for a trial.

26
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,320
It was disqualified.

27
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:08,959
My goal was to see if a normal person with a laptop could replicate a professional AI workflow.

28
00:01:08,959 --> 00:01:11,959
Without spending money, spoiler.

29
00:01:11,959 --> 00:01:13,200
Mostly yes.

30
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:20,159
But the path was messier than the YouTube Montages suggests section 2, writing and research.

31
00:01:20,159 --> 00:01:21,640
Better than expected.

32
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:27,960
For writing, I used Olamma with the Kimi K2.6 model running locally.

33
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:32,640
It required a one time download of a 60GB model file.

34
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,079
But after that it was free forever.

35
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:37,640
The writing quality surprised me.

36
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,960
Was it as poetic as Claude?

37
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:40,960
No.

38
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:42,280
Was it accurate?

39
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,280
Structured?

40
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:46,760
And fast enough to draft six articles in one day?

41
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,920
Absolutely.

42
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:51,319
For research, I used perplexity free tier for

43
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:55,879
quick fact checks and brave search AI for broader queries.

44
00:01:55,879 --> 00:02:01,280
The combination replaced 80% of what I used chat GPT for.

45
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:03,719
The 20% loss?

46
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:08,479
Complex reasoning tasks where the model needed to hold five variables in working memory

47
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:11,120
simultaneously.

48
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,120
Section 3.

49
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,519
Image and video.

50
00:02:13,519 --> 00:02:15,000
The pain point.

51
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,840
Image generation was brutal.

52
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:20,400
I used stable diffusion locally and Leonardo.

53
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,280
I free tier.

54
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:26,840
Local generation took four minutes per image on my CPU.

55
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:30,680
Leonardo gave me 150 tokens per day.

56
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,360
Which vanished in 20 minutes.

57
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:36,240
After day 10, I switched strategy.

58
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:41,439
I stopped trying to generate images and started editing existing ones using free tools

59
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:42,680
like.

60
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:45,360
Photopie and Remove.bg.

61
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,360
The result?

62
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:52,480
My thumbnails actually got better because I was forced to be intentional instead of prompting.

63
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,480
Endlessly.

64
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,080
Section 4.

65
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,880
Coding and Automation.

66
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,200
Shockingly good.

67
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,480
This was the biggest surprise.

68
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:05,280
GitHub Copilot free for students and open source maintainers aside.

69
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:08,600
I used Codium and Tabby self-hosted.

70
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:13,640
Both are free in completion quality is 85% of Copilot.

71
00:03:13,639 --> 00:03:20,519
For Automation, I built a local N8N instance and connected it to Olamma via API.

72
00:03:20,519 --> 00:03:23,599
It ran my entire content pipeline.

73
00:03:23,599 --> 00:03:29,879
Draft generation, formatting and file export with zero cloud dependency.

74
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:34,560
The only cost was the electricity running my laptop overnight.

75
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,560
Section 5.

76
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,439
The hidden cost of free.

77
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:39,479
Free AI is not free.

78
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:41,159
It costs time.

79
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:44,639
Total energy and configuration complexity.

80
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:49,719
I spent 14 hours in the first week just getting models downloaded.

81
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:52,120
Quantized and connected.

82
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:59,479
On day 17, I spent three hours debugging a memory leak in my local setup instead of working.

83
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:02,800
The free tools also have less safety netting.

84
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:07,000
When Copilot generates buggy code, it is obvious.

85
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:11,120
When your local model generates subtly wrong logic, it can take a few hours to get

86
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:13,039
three hours to catch.

87
00:04:13,039 --> 00:04:15,120
Free requires vigilance.

88
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,720
Call to action.

89
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,000
Final 30s.

90
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,399
If you want the exact free tool stack I used.

91
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:24,399
With download links and setup scripts.

92
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:26,639
It is all in the description.

93
00:04:26,639 --> 00:04:32,040
Subscribe if you want more honest experiments instead of sponsored AI hype.

94
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:36,280
And tell me, could you survive 30 days without paid AI?

95
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:40,600
Or is there one subscription you are genuinely terrified to cancel?

96
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,680
I will reply to the best answers with alternatives.
